Per-arg mesh resolution must build MeshPathIndex once and resolve every positional arg through it; the stale and list/show resolvers each reimplement this loop and must never reintroduce a per-arg corpus-reload helper (meshes_matching_path_in / matching_mesh_names_in), which turns a shell-expanded glob of hundreds of args against a large mesh set into an O(args x meshes) freeze. The compiler accepts either form, so this contract is unenforced.
